WEBVTT

1
00:00:13.518 --> 00:00:14.820
The first time
我第一次

2
00:00:15.422 --> 00:00:16.844
I felt fear
感到害怕

3
00:00:17.841 --> 00:00:19.104
I was 41 years old.
是在41岁的时候

4
00:00:20.502 --> 00:00:22.916
People have always said I was brave.
人们总是说我很勇敢

5
00:00:23.499 --> 00:00:26.118
When I was little, I'd climb the highest tree,
小时候，我可以爬最高的树

6
00:00:26.142 --> 00:00:28.662
and I'd approach any animal fearlessly.
也可以毫无畏惧得接近任何动物

7
00:00:29.821 --> 00:00:31.376
I liked challenges.
我喜欢挑战

8
00:00:32.106 --> 00:00:33.440
My father used to say,
父亲以前经常说

9
00:00:34.622 --> 00:00:39.046
"Good steel can withstand any temperature."
"好钢可以经受任何温度的烤炼。"

10
00:00:40.153 --> 00:00:43.156
And when I entered into Colombian politics,
当我进入哥伦比亚政界时

11
00:00:44.265 --> 00:00:46.746
I thought I'd be able to withstand any temperature.
我以为我能够经受任何考验

12
00:00:46.770 --> 00:00:48.941
I wanted to end corruption;
我想终结腐败

13
00:00:48.965 --> 00:00:53.144
I wanted to cut ties between politicians and drug traffickers.
我想切断政客们与贩毒者之间的联系

14
00:00:53.168 --> 00:00:55.826
The first time I was elected,
我第一次当选

15
00:00:55.850 --> 00:00:58.533
it was because I called out, by name,
是因为我大胆得说出

16
00:00:58.557 --> 00:01:01.578
corrupt and untouchable politicians.
腐败且不可冒犯的政客们的名字

17
00:01:02.172 --> 00:01:04.518
I also called out the president
我也指出了总统

18
00:01:05.388 --> 00:01:08.298
for his ties to the cartels.
和卡特尔的共谋关系

19
00:01:09.460 --> 00:01:11.587
That's when the threats started.
但从那时起我开始受到威胁

20
00:01:12.449 --> 00:01:17.781
I had to send my very young children out of the country one morning,
我不得不在一天早上把我的小孩们送出国

21
00:01:17.805 --> 00:01:21.967
hidden, all the way to the airport, in the French ambassador's armored car.
在去机场的路上，孩子们一直藏在法国大使的装甲车里

22
00:01:22.425 --> 00:01:23.805
Days later,
数天后

23
00:01:24.742 --> 00:01:27.365
I was the victim of an attack, but emerged unharmed.
我成为了一次袭击的受害者，但所幸没有受伤

24
00:01:28.944 --> 00:01:30.267
The following year,
第二年

25
00:01:31.135 --> 00:01:34.642
the Colombian people elected me with the highest number of votes.
我又被哥伦比亚人民高票选中

26
00:01:35.755 --> 00:01:39.238
I thought people applauded me because I was brave.
我想人们拥护我是因为我勇敢

27
00:01:40.224 --> 00:01:42.351
I, too, thought I was brave.
我也以为自己很勇敢

28
00:01:43.279 --> 00:01:44.683
But I wasn't.
但其实不然

29
00:01:46.714 --> 00:01:50.266
I had simply never before experienced
我只是还从未经历过

30
00:01:50.905 --> 00:01:53.145
true fear.
真正的恐惧

31
00:01:54.557 --> 00:01:55.733
That changed
但2002年2月23日那天

32
00:01:57.066 --> 00:01:59.447
on February 23, 2002.
彻底改变了我

33
00:02:01.066 --> 00:02:04.346
At the time, I was a presidential candidate in Colombia
那时，作为哥伦比亚总统候选人

34
00:02:05.029 --> 00:02:08.377
promoting my campaign agenda,
我正在准备我的竞选日程

35
00:02:08.401 --> 00:02:11.634
when I was detained by a group of armed men.
但被一群武装分子绑架

36
00:02:12.222 --> 00:02:15.037
They were wearing uniforms with military garments.
他们穿着军装式制服

37
00:02:16.410 --> 00:02:19.163
I looked at their boots; they were rubber.
我观察了他们的靴子，是橡胶的

38
00:02:19.187 --> 00:02:20.596
And I knew
我知道

39
00:02:20.620 --> 00:02:22.921
that the Colombian army wore leather boots.
哥伦比亚军队是穿皮靴的

40
00:02:23.767 --> 00:02:27.441
I knew that these were FARC guerrillas.
我得以知道他们是FARC游击队

41
00:02:28.068 --> 00:02:30.798
From that point on, everything happened very quickly.
从那时起，突然发生了很多事情

42
00:02:33.457 --> 00:02:36.963
The commando leader ordered us to stop the vehicle.
武装头目命令我们停车

43
00:02:37.891 --> 00:02:42.022
Meanwhile, one of his men stepped on an antipersonnel mine
那时他的一名成员踩在了一枚杀伤性地雷上

44
00:02:42.704 --> 00:02:44.828
and flew through the air.
被炸飞到空中

45
00:02:45.574 --> 00:02:47.574
He landed, sitting upright,
当他落回到地面上时，他直挺挺坐着

46
00:02:48.256 --> 00:02:49.905
right in front of me.
就坐在我面前

47
00:02:49.929 --> 00:02:51.929
We made eye contact
我们发生了目光接触

48
00:02:52.841 --> 00:02:55.190
and it was then that the young man understood:
那位年轻人发现

49
00:02:56.246 --> 00:02:58.729
his rubber boot with his leg still in it
他的橡皮靴连同他的双腿

50
00:02:58.753 --> 00:03:00.198
had landed far away.
被炸飞在了其他地方

51
00:03:01.744 --> 00:03:02.934
(Sighs)
（叹息）

52
00:03:04.823 --> 00:03:06.054
He started
他开始

53
00:03:08.689 --> 00:03:10.942
screaming like crazy.
疯狂叫喊

54
00:03:12.972 --> 00:03:14.141
And the truth is,
实际上

55
00:03:14.816 --> 00:03:20.960
I felt -- as I feel right now, because I'm reliving these emotions --
我当时感到－－现在也有同样的感觉，因为那些感受现在很真切

56
00:03:20.984 --> 00:03:24.617
I felt at that moment that something inside of me was breaking
那时我感到 我心里的某个东西正在破裂

57
00:03:25.540 --> 00:03:28.443
and that I was being infected with his fear.
他的恐惧影响了我

58
00:03:28.467 --> 00:03:31.331
My mind went blank and couldn't think;
我大脑一片空白，无法思考

59
00:03:31.355 --> 00:03:32.530
it was paralyzed.
我的大脑僵住了

60
00:03:33.243 --> 00:03:34.936
When I finally reacted,
当我终于回过神来时

61
00:03:36.879 --> 00:03:38.338
I said to myself,
我对自己说

62
00:03:38.716 --> 00:03:39.993
"They're going to kill me,
“他们会杀死我

63
00:03:41.128 --> 00:03:43.469
and I didn't say goodbye to my children."
而我还没跟孩子们道别。”

64
00:03:46.798 --> 00:03:50.851
As they took me into the deepest depths of the jungle,
当他们把我带进密林深处时

65
00:03:52.796 --> 00:03:54.403
the FARC soldiers announced
FARC成员宣布

66
00:03:55.169 --> 00:03:57.169
that if the government didn't negotiate,
如果政府不进行谈判

67
00:03:58.406 --> 00:03:59.650
they'd kill me.
他们就杀了我

68
00:04:00.674 --> 00:04:02.424
And I knew
而我知道

69
00:04:03.269 --> 00:04:06.421
that the government wouldn't negotiate.
政府是不会谈判的

70
00:04:07.865 --> 00:04:09.168
From that point on,
从那时起

71
00:04:09.898 --> 00:04:12.990
I went to sleep in fear every night --
我每天晚上都带着恐惧入睡－－

72
00:04:13.014 --> 00:04:14.434
cold sweats,
冒冷汗

73
00:04:15.039 --> 00:04:16.322
shaking,
发抖

74
00:04:17.187 --> 00:04:19.187
stomach ache,
胃痛

75
00:04:19.211 --> 00:04:20.468
insomnia.
失眠

76
00:04:21.793 --> 00:04:24.373
But worse than that was what was happening to my mind,
但是更糟的是我的大脑发生了变化

77
00:04:24.397 --> 00:04:28.896
because my memory was being erased: all the phone numbers,
我的记忆都被抹掉了： 所有电话号码

78
00:04:28.920 --> 00:04:30.407
addresses,
地址

79
00:04:30.431 --> 00:04:32.500
names of very dear people,
至亲的人的名字

80
00:04:32.524 --> 00:04:36.203
even significant life events.
甚至重大的生活事件

81
00:04:38.386 --> 00:04:39.708
And so,
于是

82
00:04:40.410 --> 00:04:43.394
I began to doubt myself, to doubt my mental health.
我开始怀疑自己 怀疑自己心理不健康

83
00:04:44.862 --> 00:04:47.835
And with doubt came desperation,
怀疑带来了绝望

84
00:04:48.565 --> 00:04:50.659
and with desperation came depression.
绝望带来了抑郁

85
00:04:51.787 --> 00:04:54.565
I was suffering notorious behavioral changes
我正在遭遇非常糟糕的行为性变化

86
00:04:54.589 --> 00:04:58.216
and it wasn't just paranoia in moments of panic.
在恐惧的时候，我不仅仅偏执

87
00:04:58.969 --> 00:05:01.731
It was distrust,
还充满不信任

88
00:05:02.692 --> 00:05:03.942
it was hatred,
充满仇恨

89
00:05:04.716 --> 00:05:06.637
and it was also the urge to kill.
还有杀人的冲动

90
00:05:07.574 --> 00:05:09.841
This, I realized
我意识到自己有杀人的冲动

91
00:05:09.865 --> 00:05:14.426
when they had me chained by the neck to a tree.
是在他们把我的脖子用链条拴在树上

92
00:05:15.767 --> 00:05:19.054
They kept me outside that day,
让我一直待在外面

93
00:05:20.086 --> 00:05:21.821
during a tropical downpour.
待在热带暴雨中

94
00:05:23.058 --> 00:05:28.358
I remember feeling an urgent need to use the bathroom.
我记得当时自己迫切需要去厕所

95
00:05:32.832 --> 00:05:34.369
"Whatever you have to do,
“不管你要做什么，

96
00:05:36.616 --> 00:05:38.616
you'll do in front of me,
你就在我眼皮底下做，

97
00:05:43.481 --> 00:05:44.695
bitch,"
贱人。“

98
00:05:50.871 --> 00:05:52.410
the guard screamed at me.
守卫对我吼道

99
00:06:01.121 --> 00:06:02.282
And I
而我

100
00:06:04.797 --> 00:06:07.406
decided at that moment
那时决定

101
00:06:16.660 --> 00:06:17.893
to kill him.
要杀死他

102
00:06:22.155 --> 00:06:24.823
And for days,
接下来的数天里

103
00:06:26.426 --> 00:06:30.539
I was planning, trying to find the right moment, the right way to do it,
我计划着，尝试寻找合适的时机和方式

104
00:06:30.563 --> 00:06:32.048
filled with hatred,
我的心中充满了仇恨

105
00:06:32.072 --> 00:06:33.246
filled with fear.
和恐惧

106
00:06:33.984 --> 00:06:35.776
Then suddenly,
然而突然间

107
00:06:35.800 --> 00:06:37.060
I rose up,
我清醒了过来

108
00:06:37.084 --> 00:06:38.432
snapped out of it
我改变了想法

109
00:06:39.209 --> 00:06:40.422
and thought:
我想

110
00:06:41.405 --> 00:06:43.509
"I'm not going to become one of them.
“我不要变成他们那样的人。

111
00:06:43.533 --> 00:06:45.533
I'm not going to become an assassin.
我不要当一名刺客。

112
00:06:46.470 --> 00:06:50.788
I still have enough freedom
我仍有足够的自由

113
00:06:52.756 --> 00:06:54.165
to decide
来决定

114
00:06:55.327 --> 00:06:56.721
who I want to be."
我要成为什么样的人。“

115
00:06:59.832 --> 00:07:01.645
That's when I learned that fear
那时我明白了

116
00:07:04.134 --> 00:07:06.134
brought me face to face with myself.
恐惧促使我面对自我

117
00:07:07.047 --> 00:07:08.230
It forced me
促使我

118
00:07:09.212 --> 00:07:11.674
to align my energies,
调整我的精力

119
00:07:11.698 --> 00:07:14.266
to align my meridians.
调整我的方向

120
00:07:15.321 --> 00:07:18.034
I learned that facing fear
我懂得了面对恐惧

121
00:07:19.717 --> 00:07:23.249
could become a pathway to growth.
能使人成长

122
00:07:25.550 --> 00:07:28.248
A lot of emotions arise when I talk about all of this,
在我谈论这些时我的情绪很复杂

123
00:07:28.938 --> 00:07:31.125
but when I think back,
但当我回顾过去的经历时，

124
00:07:32.601 --> 00:07:34.051
I'm able to identify
我很明确

125
00:07:34.979 --> 00:07:37.437
the steps I took to do it.
我所采取的行动

126
00:07:38.093 --> 00:07:41.494
I want to share three of them with you.
我想与大家分享其中三个

127
00:07:41.518 --> 00:07:43.592
The first
第一个是

128
00:07:45.383 --> 00:07:47.483
was to be guided by principles.
以原则为指导

129
00:07:48.426 --> 00:07:49.604
Because I realized
我意识到

130
00:07:49.628 --> 00:07:52.444
that in the midst of panic and mental block,
在处于恐慌和精神障碍中时

131
00:07:53.309 --> 00:07:56.610
if I followed my principles,
如果我遵循自己的原则

132
00:07:56.634 --> 00:07:58.313
I acted correctly.
我就会采取正确的行动

133
00:08:00.265 --> 00:08:03.436
I remember the first night
我记得在

134
00:08:03.460 --> 00:08:07.308
in a concentration camp that the guerrillas had built
在游击队建立的集中营的第一个晚上

135
00:08:07.332 --> 00:08:08.670
in the middle of the jungle,
那个集中营是建在丛林中间

136
00:08:09.448 --> 00:08:12.802
with 12-foot-high bars,
有12英尺高的栅栏

137
00:08:12.826 --> 00:08:14.431
barbed wire,
围着铁丝网

138
00:08:14.455 --> 00:08:16.795
lookouts in the four corners
四角都有守卫看守

139
00:08:16.819 --> 00:08:20.191
and armed men pointing guns at us 24 hours a day.
还有武装人员一天24小时用枪指着我们

140
00:08:21.318 --> 00:08:23.479
That morning, the first morning,
第一天早上

141
00:08:24.678 --> 00:08:27.385
some men arrived, yelling:
来了一些人，他们大喊：

142
00:08:27.409 --> 00:08:29.242
"Count off! Count off!"
“报数！报数！”

143
00:08:30.567 --> 00:08:34.746
My fellow hostages woke up, startled,
我的同伴们都被叫醒，受到了惊吓，

144
00:08:34.770 --> 00:08:38.098
and began to identify themselves in numbered sequence.
开始按顺序报数

145
00:08:38.637 --> 00:08:40.288
But when it was my turn,
轮到我时

146
00:08:41.732 --> 00:08:42.885
I said,
我说，

147
00:08:43.858 --> 00:08:45.203
"Ingrid Betancourt.
“英格丽德·贝当古

148
00:08:45.227 --> 00:08:48.265
If you want to know if I'm here, call me by my name."
如果你们想知道我是否在这里 叫我的名字。“

149
00:08:49.386 --> 00:08:51.385
The guards' fury
那个守卫非常恼怒

150
00:08:52.669 --> 00:08:55.137
was nothing compared to that of the other hostages,
而我的同伴们更加愤怒

151
00:08:55.840 --> 00:08:58.915
because, obviously they were scared --
因为很明显得，他们感到非常害怕

152
00:08:58.939 --> 00:09:00.348
we were all scared --
我们都非常害怕－－

153
00:09:00.372 --> 00:09:03.782
and they were afraid that, because of me, they would be punished.
他们害怕因为我的行为他们会遭到处罚

154
00:09:04.476 --> 00:09:05.747
But for me,
但对我来说

155
00:09:05.771 --> 00:09:12.432
beyond fear was the need to defend my identity,
除了恐惧 我必须捍卫我的身份

156
00:09:12.456 --> 00:09:16.003
to not let them turn me into a thing or a number.
不让他们把我当作 一件物品或一个数字

157
00:09:16.027 --> 00:09:17.597
That was one of the principles:
这就是其中的一个原则：

158
00:09:18.138 --> 00:09:20.138
to defend
捍卫

159
00:09:21.416 --> 00:09:23.856
what I considered to be human dignity.
我所认为的人的尊严

160
00:09:25.277 --> 00:09:27.180
But make no mistake:
但是绝不能出错：

161
00:09:27.204 --> 00:09:29.204
the guerrillas had it all
因为游击队对此

162
00:09:30.534 --> 00:09:32.181
very well analyzed --
很清楚

163
00:09:32.205 --> 00:09:34.396
they had been kidnapping for years,
他们已经从事绑架很多年

164
00:09:34.420 --> 00:09:37.897
and they had developed a technique
他们已经掌握了

165
00:09:38.865 --> 00:09:40.470
to break us,
让人崩溃的

166
00:09:40.494 --> 00:09:42.254
to defeat us, to divide us.
让人失败和分裂的技巧

167
00:09:42.835 --> 00:09:44.062
And so,
因此，

168
00:09:44.708 --> 00:09:46.370
the second step
第二步

169
00:09:47.977 --> 00:09:50.984
was to learn how to build supportive trust,
是学会建立相互支持的信任

170
00:09:51.008 --> 00:09:53.412
to learn how to unite.
学会团结

171
00:09:55.268 --> 00:09:58.351
The jungle is like a different planet.
丛林是一个完全不一样世界，

172
00:09:59.533 --> 00:10:02.118
It's a world
那里到处都是

173
00:10:04.023 --> 00:10:06.366
of shadows, of rain,
阴影，大雨，

174
00:10:07.937 --> 00:10:12.527
with the hum of millions of bugs --
很成千上万的虫子发出嗡嗡声-

175
00:10:12.551 --> 00:10:14.756
majiña ants, bullet ants.
有麻吉蚁、子弹蚁

176
00:10:15.496 --> 00:10:18.771
I didn't stop scratching a single day while I was in the jungle.
我在那里的每一天都觉得浑身发痒

177
00:10:21.032 --> 00:10:25.619
And of course, there were tarantulas, scorpions, anacondas ...
当然，那里也有狼蛛、蝎子、水蟒等等

178
00:10:25.643 --> 00:10:29.846
I once came face to face with a 24-foot long anaconda
有一次我直面一只24英尺长的水蟒

179
00:10:29.870 --> 00:10:32.024
that could have swallowed me in one bite.
它本来可以将我一口吞掉

180
00:10:32.048 --> 00:10:33.230
Jaguars ...
那里还有美洲虎

181
00:10:33.921 --> 00:10:35.921
But I want to tell you
但是我想要告诉你们的是，

182
00:10:35.945 --> 00:10:39.992
that none of these animals did us as much harm
任何一种动物对我们造成的伤害

183
00:10:40.741 --> 00:10:42.058
as the human beings.
都比不上人类对我们造成的伤害。

184
00:10:46.979 --> 00:10:49.205
The guerrillas terrorized us.
游击队恐吓我们，

185
00:10:49.665 --> 00:10:52.848
They spread rumors.
他们传播谣言，

186
00:10:53.514 --> 00:10:56.408
Among the hostages, they sparked betrayals,
他们让人质彼此背叛

187
00:10:57.087 --> 00:10:58.555
jealousy,
嫉妒

188
00:10:59.111 --> 00:11:00.404
resentment,
怨恨

189
00:11:01.135 --> 00:11:02.386
mistrust.
误解

190
00:11:03.595 --> 00:11:10.069
The first time I escaped for a long time was with Lucho.
我第一次长时间逃离是和卢科

191
00:11:10.093 --> 00:11:12.902
Lucho had been a hostage for two years longer than I had.
卢科被关押进来的时间比我还长2年。

192
00:11:13.557 --> 00:11:16.589
We decided to tie ourselves up
我们决定用绳子

193
00:11:17.510 --> 00:11:19.157
with ropes
将我们捆起来

194
00:11:19.181 --> 00:11:23.598
to have the strength to lower ourselves into that dark water
将我们降落到黑水中

195
00:11:23.622 --> 00:11:26.646
full of piranhas and alligators.
那里到处都是水虎鱼和短吻鳄

196
00:11:28.271 --> 00:11:32.742
What we did was, during the day, we would hide in the mangroves.
白天的时候，我们藏在红树林中，

197
00:11:33.702 --> 00:11:35.369
And at night,
晚上

198
00:11:35.393 --> 00:11:37.446
we would leave, get in the water,
我们离开红树林，再回到水中，

199
00:11:38.377 --> 00:11:41.612
and we would swim and let the current carry us.
我们可以游泳，并让水流拖着我们

200
00:11:42.778 --> 00:11:44.972
That went on for several days.
我们有好几天都是这样的。

201
00:11:45.615 --> 00:11:47.392
But Lucho
但是后来卢科

202
00:11:49.004 --> 00:11:50.362
became sick.
生病了

203
00:11:50.386 --> 00:11:51.700
He was diabetic,
他患有糖尿病

204
00:11:52.410 --> 00:11:54.089
and he fell into a diabetic coma.
发生了糖尿病性昏迷

205
00:11:55.148 --> 00:11:59.356
So the guerrillas captured us.
所以游击队逮到了我们

206
00:12:00.618 --> 00:12:03.839
But after having lived through that with Lucho,
但是，自从和卢科经历了那次逃离，

207
00:12:04.702 --> 00:12:07.378
after having faced fear together, united,
我们一起面对恐惧，团结一致，

208
00:12:08.371 --> 00:12:11.919
not punishment, not violence -- nothing --
惩罚，暴力甚至任何事

209
00:12:12.711 --> 00:12:16.025
could ever again divide us.
都不会使我们产生分歧

210
00:12:19.128 --> 00:12:20.914
What's certain is,
可以确定的是

211
00:12:20.938 --> 00:12:24.734
all the guerrillas' manipulation was so damaging to us
游击队对我们的操控给我们造成了非常大的伤害，

212
00:12:26.057 --> 00:12:27.839
that even today,
以至于直到今天

213
00:12:28.888 --> 00:12:30.888
among some of the hostages
当时被关押的

214
00:12:32.586 --> 00:12:33.888
from back then,
那些人质之间

215
00:12:35.531 --> 00:12:37.096
tensions linger,
仍然关系紧张

216
00:12:38.104 --> 00:12:41.579
passed down from all that poison
时游击队制造的毒害

217
00:12:43.586 --> 00:12:45.586
that the guerrillas created.
被流传了下来

218
00:12:47.745 --> 00:12:49.047
The third step
第三步

219
00:12:50.459 --> 00:12:52.856
is very important to me,
对我来说非常重要

220
00:12:52.880 --> 00:12:55.240
and it's a gift that I want to give to you.
也是我想送给你们的礼物

221
00:12:56.163 --> 00:13:00.725
The third step is to learn how to develop faith.
第三步是学会如何发展信仰

222
00:13:02.994 --> 00:13:06.761
I want to explain it like this:
我想这样解释

223
00:13:07.610 --> 00:13:09.065
Jhon Frank Pinchao
约翰 弗兰克 平科

224
00:13:09.929 --> 00:13:12.257
was a police officer
是一位警官

225
00:13:12.281 --> 00:13:14.701
who had been a hostage for more than eight years.
他被关押的时间长于8年

226
00:13:15.385 --> 00:13:19.291
He was famous for being the biggest scaredy-cat of us all.
他因为是胆小鬼而出名

227
00:13:22.163 --> 00:13:24.918
But Pincho -- I called him "Pincho" --
但是平科-我叫他平科-

228
00:13:24.942 --> 00:13:29.597
Pincho decided that he wanted to escape.
平科决定他要逃离

229
00:13:30.192 --> 00:13:31.555
And he asked me to help him.
他请求我帮助他

230
00:13:31.579 --> 00:13:35.084
By that point, I basically had a master's degree in escape attempts.
那个时候，我已经取得了“尝试逃跑”的硕士学位

231
00:13:35.108 --> 00:13:36.533
(Laughter)
（笑声）

232
00:13:37.012 --> 00:13:38.244
So
所以

233
00:13:40.014 --> 00:13:41.749
we got started but we had a delay,
我们便开始行动，但是行动被延迟了

234
00:13:41.773 --> 00:13:44.432
because first, Pincho had to learn how to swim.
因为平科首先必须学会游泳，

235
00:13:45.257 --> 00:13:50.149
And we had to carry out all these preparations in total secrecy.
而且我们必须对我们的行动计划完全保秘

236
00:13:50.855 --> 00:13:54.233
Anyway, when we finally had everything ready,
总之，最后我们准备好了所有的事情

237
00:13:54.257 --> 00:13:58.427
Pincho came up to me one afternoon and said,
平科有一天下午找到我，他说

238
00:13:58.451 --> 00:14:01.610
"Ingrid, suppose I'm in the jungle,
英格丽德，假设我正在丛林中，

239
00:14:01.634 --> 00:14:05.255
and I go around and around in circles, and I can't find the way out.
我一直在转圈圈，找不到出去的路

240
00:14:05.279 --> 00:14:06.449
What do I do?"
我应该做什么？

241
00:14:07.846 --> 00:14:09.023
"Pincho,
平科

242
00:14:10.571 --> 00:14:11.878
you grab a phone,
你可以拿起一个电话

243
00:14:13.060 --> 00:14:14.679
and you call the man upstairs."
打电话给天上的人

244
00:14:15.831 --> 00:14:18.958
"Ingrid, you know I don't believe in God."
英格丽德，你知道我不信仰上帝

245
00:14:23.577 --> 00:14:26.286
"God doesn't care. He'll still help you."
上帝不介意，他仍然会帮助你

246
00:14:29.079 --> 00:14:32.177
(Applause)
（鼓掌）

247
00:14:35.447 --> 00:14:37.968
It rained all night that night.
那晚一晚上都在下雨

248
00:14:39.024 --> 00:14:40.505
The following morning,
第二天早上

249
00:14:41.738 --> 00:14:43.813
the camp woke up to a big commotion,
整个集中营醒在一片骚动中醒来

250
00:14:43.837 --> 00:14:46.521
because Pincho had fled.
因为平科逃跑了

251
00:14:46.545 --> 00:14:49.306
They made us dismantle the camp, and we started marching.
他们迫使我们拆除营地，开始跋涉，

252
00:14:49.330 --> 00:14:50.593
During the march,
在行走中，

253
00:14:52.149 --> 00:14:56.705
the head guerrillas told us that Pincho had died,
游击队首领告诉我们平科已经死了

254
00:14:56.729 --> 00:14:59.864
and that they had found his remains
他们已经找到了他的身体的一些残余

255
00:14:59.888 --> 00:15:01.419
eaten by an anaconda.
他的遗体被水蟒吃了

256
00:15:04.379 --> 00:15:06.073
Seventeen days passed --
17天后

257
00:15:06.097 --> 00:15:11.448
and believe me, I counted them, because they were torture for me.
相信我，我确定数了是17天，因为那些天对我来说简直是一种莫大的折磨

258
00:15:13.980 --> 00:15:15.980
But on the seventeenth day,
但是第17天

259
00:15:18.003 --> 00:15:19.919
the news exploded from the radio:
收音机里有一条爆炸式新闻

260
00:15:19.943 --> 00:15:23.157
Pincho was free and obviously alive.
平科事实上已经自由了，很显然他还活着

261
00:15:24.024 --> 00:15:27.528
And this was the first thing he said:
他说的第一句话是：

262
00:15:28.872 --> 00:15:30.872
"I know my fellow hostages are listening.
我知道我的同伴们在收听

263
00:15:31.633 --> 00:15:33.127
Ingrid,
英格丽德

264
00:15:33.151 --> 00:15:34.873
I did what you told me.
我按你说的做了

265
00:15:34.897 --> 00:15:36.568
I called the man upstairs,
我给天上的人打电话了

266
00:15:36.592 --> 00:15:40.133
and he sent me the patrol that rescued me from the jungle."
他派来了巡逻队将我从丛林中解救了出来

267
00:15:43.284 --> 00:15:46.297
That was an extraordinary moment,
那是一个不同寻常的时刻

268
00:15:46.321 --> 00:15:47.487
because ...
因为

269
00:15:48.098 --> 00:15:50.098
obviously fear is contagious.
恐惧会蔓延

270
00:15:50.729 --> 00:15:52.159
But faith is, too.
但是信仰同样如此

271
00:15:52.183 --> 00:15:54.822
Faith isn't rational or emotional.
信仰不是理性的也不是感性的

272
00:15:55.631 --> 00:15:56.813
Faith
信仰

273
00:15:57.860 --> 00:16:00.476
is an exercise of the will.
是毅力的一种表现

274
00:16:01.087 --> 00:16:03.721
It's the discipline of the will.
是毅力的一种训练

275
00:16:04.173 --> 00:16:07.644
It's what allows us to transform everything that we are --
信仰可以让我们发生很大改变

276
00:16:07.668 --> 00:16:09.966
our weaknesses, our frailties,
可以将我们的弱项和脆弱

277
00:16:09.990 --> 00:16:11.580
into strength, into power.
转变为强项和力量

278
00:16:11.604 --> 00:16:13.604
It's truly a transformation.
是一种实实在在的转变

279
00:16:14.641 --> 00:16:17.502
It's what gives us the strength
信仰给予我们力量

280
00:16:17.526 --> 00:16:18.907
to stand up
让我们直面

281
00:16:20.264 --> 00:16:21.469
in the face of fear
恐惧

282
00:16:22.484 --> 00:16:24.208
look above it,
不被恐惧困住

283
00:16:24.232 --> 00:16:25.630
and see beyond it.
超越恐惧

284
00:16:28.042 --> 00:16:30.042
I hope you remember that,
我希望你们能够记住这一点

285
00:16:31.605 --> 00:16:33.440
because I know we all need
因为我认为我们都需要

286
00:16:34.463 --> 00:16:37.457
to connect with that strength we have inside of us
与我们内在的那股力量发生连接

287
00:16:38.057 --> 00:16:42.499
for the times when there's a storm raging around our boat.
让我们度过艰难的时期

288
00:16:43.260 --> 00:16:47.669
Many, many, many, many years passed
许多许多年之后

289
00:16:49.399 --> 00:16:54.008
before I could return to my house.
我才得以回到我的家

290
00:16:55.936 --> 00:17:00.965
But when they took us, handcuffed, into the helicopter
当他们给我们戴上手铐坐进直升飞机时

291
00:17:00.989 --> 00:17:03.044
that finally took us out of the jungle,
他们终于将我们带离了丛林，

292
00:17:03.068 --> 00:17:06.313
everything happened as quickly as when they kidnapped me.
所有事发生的如此之快，就像他们绑架我时一样

293
00:17:07.797 --> 00:17:09.429
In an instant,
一眨眼之间

294
00:17:09.453 --> 00:17:13.476
I saw the guerrilla commander at my feet,
我看到游击队队长站在地面上

295
00:17:13.500 --> 00:17:14.725
gagged,
哑口无言

296
00:17:15.566 --> 00:17:17.832
and the rescue leader,
而救援队队长

297
00:17:19.010 --> 00:17:20.174
yelling:
高呼

298
00:17:20.927 --> 00:17:24.342
"We're the Colombian army!
“我们是哥伦比亚军队！

299
00:17:24.367 --> 00:17:26.746
You are free!"
“你们自由了”

300
00:17:28.303 --> 00:17:29.841
The shriek
我们所有人

301
00:17:30.620 --> 00:17:32.692
that came out of all of us
发出了尖叫声

302
00:17:32.716 --> 00:17:34.707
when we regained our freedom,
因为我们重获了自由

303
00:17:35.201 --> 00:17:39.772
continues to vibrate in me to this day.
直到今天，我仍然能感受到尖叫声在我的胸腔内振动

304
00:17:42.089 --> 00:17:43.260
Now,
现在

305
00:17:44.363 --> 00:17:47.570
I know they can divide all of us,
我知道他们可以使我们所有人发生分歧

306
00:17:47.594 --> 00:17:50.011
they can manipulate us all with fear.
他们可以以恐惧操控我们

307
00:17:52.646 --> 00:17:56.914
The "No" vote on the peace referendum in Colombia;
哥伦比亚为和平进行全民投票中的否决票

308
00:17:56.938 --> 00:17:58.707
Brexit;
英国脱欧

309
00:17:58.731 --> 00:18:02.478
the idea of a wall between Mexico and the United States;
想在墨西哥和美国之间建一堵墙

310
00:18:03.143 --> 00:18:04.825
Islamic terrorism --
伊斯兰恐怖主义

311
00:18:04.849 --> 00:18:09.146
they're all examples of using fear politically
这些都是为政治目的使用恐惧的例子

312
00:18:09.855 --> 00:18:12.437
to divide and recruit us.
以恐惧使人们产生分歧并操控人们

313
00:18:14.190 --> 00:18:16.190
We all feel fear.
我们都会感到恐惧

314
00:18:16.912 --> 00:18:20.279
But we can all avoid being recruited
但是我们可以避免被恐惧所操控

315
00:18:21.254 --> 00:18:26.366
using the resources we have -- our principles, unity, faith.
我们需要利用我们所具有的资源，包括原则，团结，信仰

316
00:18:27.659 --> 00:18:31.267
Yes, fear is part of the human condition,
恐惧是人不可或缺的一部分

317
00:18:31.291 --> 00:18:34.570
as well as being necessary for survival.
是生存所必须的

318
00:18:35.205 --> 00:18:36.944
But above all,
但是，最重要的是

319
00:18:36.968 --> 00:18:41.724
it's the guide by which each of us builds
恐惧指引我们每一个人建立

320
00:18:42.574 --> 00:18:45.742
our identity, our personality.
身份和个性

321
00:18:48.649 --> 00:18:55.629
It's true, I was 41 years old the first time I felt fear,
坦白说，41岁时我才第一次感到恐惧

322
00:18:55.653 --> 00:18:59.233
and feeling fear was not my decision.
感到恐惧不是我决定的

323
00:19:00.061 --> 00:19:04.753
But it was my decision what to do with that fear.
但是我可以决定如何面对恐惧

324
00:19:07.054 --> 00:19:10.466
You can survive
你可以充满恐惧得

325
00:19:11.460 --> 00:19:14.281
crawling along, fearful.
生存下来

326
00:19:14.898 --> 00:19:16.378
But you can also
但是你也可以

327
00:19:17.847 --> 00:19:20.382
rise above the fear,
战胜恐惧

328
00:19:20.406 --> 00:19:23.218
rise up, spread your wings,
振作起来，张开双臂

329
00:19:23.242 --> 00:19:27.919
and soar, fly high, high, high, high, until you reach the stars,
翱翔，飞得高高得，直到你可以碰到星星

330
00:19:27.943 --> 00:19:30.969
where all of us want to go.
那是我们每个人都想要去的地方

331
00:19:33.367 --> 00:19:34.519
Thank you.
谢谢

332
00:19:34.543 --> 00:19:38.351
(Applause)
（鼓掌）